  "text": "Given a combinatorial line ℓ : [CITATION_1] → [CITATION_2] n , we define its length |ℓ| to be the number of coordinates 1 ≤ i ≤ n for which ℓ i (x) varies with x. For example, the line given by ℓ(x) = (3, x, 1, x, 4) has length 2. (To justify this terminology, note that |ℓ| is the Hamming distance between the two endpoints ℓ(1) and ℓ(4), or indeed between any two points of ℓ.)",
